io.spine.tools.validate.code

Interface Expression<R>

  • Type Parameters:
    R - the type of the value yielded by this expression; the type parameter is unused and serves for clarification purposes only
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    BooleanExpression, CodeExpression, FieldAccess, MessageAccess, NewViolation, VoidExpression

    public interface Expression<R>
    A Java code structure which may yield a value.

    The type parameter R is not used directly in the definition of Expression API. R signifies the return type of the Java code expression represented by a given instance of Expression type. For example, if the Java code constructs a list of strings, the expression should be parametrized as Expression<List<String>>.

    Descendants may choose to utilize the type parameter. In such a case, the party relying on the type parameter value must check for an absent parameter (i.e. bound by java.lang.Object).
